{
  "text": "is a bounded operator on L 2 (X) for Im \u03bb 0. Mazzeo and Melrose proved in [CITATION_1] Theorem 7 .1] that R(\u03bb) has a meromorphic extension to C\\ i 2 N, N = {1, 2, \u00b7 \u00b7 \u00b7 } as operators from L 2 comp (X) to L 2 loc (X). The poles of the meromorphic extension are called resonance. Guillarmou clarified in [CITATION_2] that i 2 N are essential singularities of R(\u03bb), unless the metric g is asymptotically even. Hence in general, the behavior of the resonances could be quite complicated near the positive real axis.",
  "correct_citation": {
